ABC quoted Australian Federal Police as saying the drugs arrived by sea cargo to Melbourne from South Africa on December 5. They were then moved to Sydney where they were tracked and three men were arrested on February 5. A fourth man was arrested in Melbourne on Wednesday this week.The drugs were in a seven-inch thick metal crate.One of the suspects is a 75-year-old South African citizen.Yusuf Abramjee a well-known SA anti-crime activist tweeted that the man comes from Laudium near Pretoria.Why were the drugs not detected in SA? @SAPoliceService https://t.co/HNogRBgCAZ Yusuf Abramjee (@Abramjee) 9 March 2017 Why were the drugs not detected in SA? @SAPoliceService https://t.co/HNogRBgCAZ